Hi James,

Thanks for your email. Do you have bunkering records for the cargo so that we can offer you a better price? Please provide the following information:
1. IMO (Certificate of Inspection);
2. Country of Registry;
3. Year Built;
4. BW (Lightship);
5. DWT;
6. Type of Fuel.

Kindly provide the above details to proceed. Many thanks.

Best regards,
Kim

Hi Kim,

Please find the bunkering records below:
IMO: 9632932;
Country of Registry: Marshall Islands;
Year Built: 2012;
BW: 30,299;
DWT: 45,384;
Type of Fuel: HFO 380.

Best,
James

Dear Jonathan,

To proceed with reserving the vessel, please find below the list of required documents:

1. Bill of Lading, 1 set;
2. P&I Club certificate, 1 set;
3. A1 Tanker certificate, 1 set;
4. Charter Party, 1 set;
5. Release of any attachments or liabilities and other documents as may be requested by the mortgagee. A mortgagee's consent may be required.
6. Master's account, 1 set;
7. Draft survey, 1 set;
8. Stability Certificate, 1 set;
9. Safety equipment certificates, 1 set;
10. MCA Authorization to use electronic chart display and information system (ECDIS), 1 set;
11. Oil record book, 1 set;
12. Third-party damage report and certificates, 1 set;
13. All maritime papers associated with the vessel.

Please ensure all documents are complete and forwarded to our team.

Best regards,
Mr. Liang
